83
00:04:27,004 --> 00:04:28,614
at very, very high altitudes,

84
00:04:28,615 --> 00:04:31,554
typically what a spacecraft
has to go through

85
00:04:31,555 --> 00:04:34,284
when it comes back
from a spaceflight on orbit.

86
00:04:34,285 --> 00:04:39,284
So, very useful data
for future space programs

87
00:04:39,285 --> 00:04:40,536
run by NASA.

88
00:04:41,914 --> 00:04:44,133
Well, back to commercial companies

89
00:04:44,134 --> 00:04:48,134
